<bibRefCitation id="FD35E7E5354BFFEBFEFA89B854EED2A3" author="Freidberg, A." box="[301,491,1479,1506]" pageId="5" pageNumber="458" pagination="54 - 70" refId="ref11259" refString="Freidberg, A. 2016. New taxa of Carpomyini, with special emphasis on Goniglossum (Diptera: Tephritidae: Trypetinae). Zootaxa, 4144 (1), 54 - 70. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4144.1. 2." type="journal article" year="2016">Freidberg, 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="991B9A14354BFFEBFF348A78548DD1C3" blockId="5.[174,1232,1543,1666]" pageId="5" pageNumber="458">
Remarks. This species was recently recognized and described by 
<bibRefCitation id="FD35E7E5354BFFEBFBD68A7851CED163" author="Freidberg, A." box="[1025,1227,1543,1570]" pageId="5" pageNumber="458" pagination="54 - 70" refId="ref11259" refString="Freidberg, A. 2016. New taxa of Carpomyini, with special emphasis on Goniglossum (Diptera: Tephritidae: Trypetinae). Zootaxa, 4144 (1), 54 - 70. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4144.1. 2." type="journal article" year="2016">Freidberg (2016)</bibRefCitation>
; its distribution apparently does not exceed the one mapped in that paper. As we consider 
<taxonomicName id="5EA4E197354BFFEBFF798A385446D120" box="[174,323,1607,1633]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Goniglossum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ABD04606354BFFEBFF798A385446D120" box="[174,323,1607,1633]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="458">Goniglossum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(and 
<taxonomicName id="5EA4E197354BFFEBFE5F8A385727D120" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1910" box="[392,546,1607,1633]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Myiopardalis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ABD04606354BFFEBFE5F8A385727D120" box="[392,546,1607,1633]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="458">Myiopardalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as subgenera within 
<taxonomicName id="5EA4E197354BFFEBFCF18A3856A5D120" box="[806,928,1607,1633]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Carpomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ABD04606354BFFEBFCF18A3856A5D120" box="[806,928,1607,1633]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="458">Carpomya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5EA4E197354BFFEBFC798A3856F2D120" authorityName="Freidberg" authorityYear="2016" box="[942,1015,1607,1634]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Goniglossum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="liat">
<emphasis id="ABD04606354BFFEBFC798A3856C7D120" box="[942,962,1607,1633]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="458">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="ABD04606354BFFEBFC078A3856F2D120" box="[976,1015,1607,1633]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="458">liat</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also transferred to the latter genus.
</paragraph>
